    "IntroductionNLP is a crucial branch of AI dedicated to enabling computers to comprehend, generate, and manipulate human language [1][2][3].",
    "The development of NLP has evolved over time, from early rule-based language processing to statistical and machine learning methods, ultimately culminating in modern NLP techniques consisting of deep learning [4] and neural networks.",
    "In earlier times, researchers mainly relied on rule-based or statistical methods to process language.",
    "With the advancement of machine learning, techniques like SVM and Random Forest were introduced to NLP for various tasks, for example, text classification and sentiment analysis.",
